he idea of the United States as a new Israel and sheds new light on our understanding of the nation’s origins and culture during the founding and antebellum decades.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBible and politicsxHistoryxUnited States. 0aBible and politicszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aNationalismxHistoryxUnited States. 0aNationalismzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aPolitical culturexHistoryxUnited States. 0aPolitical culturezUnited StatesxHistory. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018841740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300188417423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300188417/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles